---
/**
 * /about — About page with data sources and full attribution
 */
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="About Bird Garden — data sources, attribution, and the project behind the site.">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1 class="page-title">About Bird Garden</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-layout" style="padding-bottom: var(--space-16);">
      <p style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7;">
        Bird Garden helps you discover native plants that attract birds to your garden throughout
        the year. Plan your plantings by region and month, listen to recordings, and share your
        garden with others.
      </p>
      <p>
        All plant and bird data, song recordings, and photographs are sourced from freely-licensed,
        public-domain or Creative Commons datasets. Nothing is behind a paywall, and nothing is sent
        to any third-party server — region detection happens entirely in your browser.
      </p>

      <h2 id="data-sources" style="margin-top: var(--space-10);">Data Sources</h2>

      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-6); margin-top: var(--space-6);">

        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-base); margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);">
            <a href="https://xeno-canto.org" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
               style="color: var(--color-primary); text-decoration: underline;">
              Xeno-canto
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted);">
            Community-built database of bird sound recordings from around the world.
            Bird Garden uses only recordings shared under CC0 (public domain) and CC-BY 3.0/4.0 licenses.
            Individual recordist attribution is displayed on each bird's detail page.
          </p>
          <p style="margin: var(--space-2) 0 0; font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-text-subtle);">
            License: CC0 · CC-BY 3.0 · CC-BY 4.0 — per recording
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-base); margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);">
            <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
               style="color: var(--color-primary); text-decoration: underline;">
              Wikimedia Commons
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted);">
            Free media repository used for bird and plant photographs.
            Images are fetched via the Wikipedia API and filtered to permissively-licensed works.
            Photographer attribution and license links appear on each species page.
          </p>
          <p style="margin: var(--space-2) 0 0; font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-text-subtle);">
            License: varies — CC-BY, CC-BY-SA, CC0 — per image
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-base); margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);">
            Bird and Plant Data
          </h3>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted);">
            Species lists, habitat preferences, seasonal presence, and plant-bird attraction data
            were compiled from publicly available ornithological and horticultural literature,
            including USDA PLANTS Database taxonomy and eBird occurrence data.
            Conservation status designations follow the
            <a href="https://www.iucnredlist.org" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
               style="color: var(--color-primary);">IUCN Red List</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-base); margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);">
            USDA Hardiness Zones
          </h3>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted);">
            Plant hardiness zone ranges follow the
            <a href="https://planthardiness.ars.usda.gov" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
               style="color: var(--color-primary);">USDA Plant Hardiness Zone Map</a>
            (2023 edition). Zones are used to indicate geographic suitability, not climate predictions.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <h2 id="attribution" style="margin-top: var(--space-10);">Media Attribution</h2>
      <p>
        Every song recording and photograph displayed on Bird Garden carries attribution to its
        creator. Attribution is shown:
      </p>
      <ul style="margin-top: var(--space-3); padding-left: var(--space-6); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-2);">
        <li>
          On bird detail pages, below each AudioPlayer: recordist name, recording location and date,
          and a link to the original Xeno-canto page with the full license text.
        </li>
        <li>
          On bird and plant detail pages, in the image caption: photographer name (from Wikimedia
          Commons <code>extmetadata.Artist</code>) and license name.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
        If you believe a piece of media has been included in error or with incorrect attribution,
        please
        <a href="https://github.com/ArdentCascades/birdgarden/issues" rel="noopener noreferrer"
           target="_blank" style="color: var(--color-primary);">open an issue on GitHub</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 id="privacy" style="margin-top: var(--space-10);">Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Bird Garden does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. Your selected region
        is saved in your browser's <code>localStorage</code> and never leaves your device.
        Garden plant lists are stored locally and optionally shared via URL — no account is required.
      </p>
      <p>
        Geolocation (the "Use my location" button) is browser-initiated, requires explicit user
        permission, and coordinates are used only client-side to identify the nearest region.
        Coordinates are never sent to the Bird Garden server.
      </p>

      <h2 id="open-source" style="margin-top: var(--space-10);">Open Source</h2>
      <p>
        Bird Garden is open source. The code is available on
        <a href="https://github.com/ArdentCascades/birdgarden" rel="noopener noreferrer"
           target="_blank" style="color: var(--color-primary);">GitHub</a>.
        Built with <a href="https://astro.build" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
          style="color: var(--color-primary);">Astro</a>,
        <a href="https://preactjs.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
          style="color: var(--color-primary);">Preact</a>,
        and <a href="https://bun.sh" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
          style="color: var(--color-primary);">Bun</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
